The paper deals with using CNNs for scene classification in surveillance footage, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of different CNN architectures and network visualization techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the application of CNNs in surveillance and security-related tasks implies a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
